      "query_text": "Where should I eat downtown tonight?",
      "response_text": "I'm your Nevada County concierge! I can help you find restaurants, galleries, events, and things to do around here. We have three main historic downtown areas, so depending on where you are parked, here are my top recommendations for tonight:\n\n### **Downtown Nevada City**\nIf you are looking for a lively atmosphere, you can't go wrong with these local favorites:\n*   **[[Three Forks Bakery & Brewing Co.|three-forks-bakery-brewing-co]]**: Fantastic wood-fired pizzas and craft beer. They focus on local ingredients, fitting right into the local ritual of supporting our regional farmers {{MUSE|rural-is-the-new-cool|“...downtown Nevada City rituals that feel like they’ve always existed.”}}.\n*   **[[Friar Tucks Restaurant & Bar|friar-tucks-restaurant-bar]]**: A staple on the corner of Pine and Commercial Street known for its warm atmosphere and great fondue.\n*   **[[Lefty’s Grill|leftys-grill]]**: A wonderful spot with a diverse menu, often featuring fresh, seasonal dishes.\n\n### **Downtown Grass Valley**\nThe dining scene in Grass Valley offers a rich variety of flavors:\n*   **[[Cirino’s at Main Street|cirinos-at-main-street]]**: Famous for their Italian-inspired fare and their signature Bloody Marys. \n*   **[[Watershed Restaurant|watershed-restaurant]]**: A \"Slow Food\" inspired experience that highlights the best of the region's produce.\n*   **[[The Holbrooke Hotel|the-holbrooke-hotel]]**: Eat in a piece of history! This is one of the oldest hotels in the state and offers a refined, atmospheric dining experience.\n\n### **Historic Downtown Truckee**\nIf you are up in the mountains, Truckee has some world-class options:\n*   **[[Pianeta Ristorante|pianeta-ristorante]]**: A cozy, high-end Italian spot that is perfect for a cold winter night. \n*   **[[Moody’s Bistro Bar and Beats|moodys-bistro-bar-beats]]**: Excellent food paired with a great bar and often live jazz.\n*   **[[Cottonwood Restaurant & Bar|cottonwood-restaurant-bar]]**: This restaurant overlooks the downtown lights fr",
